The '''National Treatment Purchase Fund''' (NTPF) is an [[Government of Ireland|Irish government]] body which was established to decrease waiting lists in the Irish public [[Healthcare system|healthcare]] system.
The Fund was established under Statutory Instrument 179 - National Treatment Purchase Fund (Establishment) Order, 2004, and the Nursing Homes Support Scheme Act (2009).<ref>http://www.ntpf.ie/home/about.htm</ref> The NTPF reduced waiting times for [[medical procedures|procedures]] from between 2 and 5 years in 2002<ref>[http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/mhojkfojauey/ BreakingNews.ie – ''Over 100,000 patients treated under NTPF scheme'']</ref> to an average of 2.4 months in 2009.<ref>[http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2009/1201/breaking64.htm The Irish Times – ''Patient waiting times decrease'']</ref>
